description.p:
EP2959808 discloses a coffee machine comprising:


a source of pressurized water;

a heater connected to the source of pressurized water and to the dispensing nozzles;

a dispensing valve disposed between the heater and the dispensing nozzles; and

an additional valve disposed between the source of pressurized water and the heater.

Additional features of the invention will appear clearer from the following description, which refers to merely illustrative, not limiting embodiments, as illustrated in the appended drawings, wherein:


Fig. 1 is a block diagram that diagrammatically illustrates a first embodiment of a coffee machine according to the invention;

Fig. 2 is a block diagram that diagrammatically illustrates a second embodiment of a coffee machine according to the invention;

Fig. 3 is chart with the time value in seconds on the abscissa axis, and the flow percentage on the ordinate axis, which illustrates the trend of the flow as a function of the time during a dispensing time of the pre-infusion valve;

Fig. 4 is the same chart as Fig. 3, which illustrates the trend of the flow as a function of the time during a pre-infusion cycle of the pre-infusion valve.

Starting from a time 0, the valve starts opening gradually;


after 0.8 seconds, the valve is partially open in such a way to obtain a flow of 40% relative to the maximum flow obtained when the valve is completely opened;

after 2 seconds, the valve is completely open in such a way to permit the maximum flow;

the valve is kept completely open for 1 second;

after 3 seconds, the valve starts closing gradually;

after 4.3 seconds, the valve is partially closed in such a way to permit a flow of 60% relative to the maximum flow obtained when the valve is completely open; and

after 5 seconds, the valve is completely closed and the flow is interrupted.

claim.claim-text:
Coffee machine (1) comprising: - a filter holder (2) suitable for containing at least one coffee dose (3), - a dispensing unit (4) suitable for receiving the filter holder (2); said dispensing unit being provided with dispensing nozzles (40) suitable for sending a flow of hot water on the coffee dose (3) contained in the filter holder, - a water system (5) provided with a pump (50) to supply pressurized water to said dispensing nozzles (40) of the dispensing unit, - a heater (6) disposed in said water system (5) to heat the water to be supplied to the dispensing nozzles (40), - a dispensing valve (7) disposed in said water system between the heater (6) and the dispensing nozzles (40) to enable/disable the supply of hot water to said dispensing nozzles, - a pre-infusion valve (9) disposed in said water system (5) upstream said dispensing valve (7), and - a control unit (10) comprising actuation means (11) to actuate said pre-infusion valve (9), wherein said pre-infusion valve (9) is a two-way electrovalve of programmable proportional type, comprising a shutter suitable for gradually opening and closing the communication between the two ways of the valve proportionally to a command signal (S) sent by said actuation means (11);
characterized in that
the actuation means (11) and the pre-infusion valve (9) are configured in such a way to have: - a dispensing time (Te) from the moment when the pre-infusion valve is opened to the moment when the pre-infusion valve is closed, - an opening time (T1) from the moment when the pre-infusion valve starts opening to the moment when the pre-infusion valve is completely open, - a maximum flow time (T2) in which the pre-infusion valve is completely open, and - a closing time (T3) from the moment when the pre-infusion valve starts closing to the moment when the pre-infusion valve is completely closed; wherein the opening time (T1) is higher than 1/3 of the dispensing time (Te), the maximum flow time (T2) is lower than 1/3 of the dispensing time (Te), and the closing time (T3) is higher than 1/3 of the dispensing time (Te).
